					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can forget EPROMs and get some NOR Flash chips instead unless you fancy waiting 45ish minutes each time when erasing EPROMs with your favorite UV eraser. There might be some pinout differences though and you may have to reroute a VPP line to accomodate a new address line, but that you'll find out when comparing datasheets.<br />020 parts are 2MBit, 040 are 8MBit. 27Cxxx are EPROMs, 28Fxxx and 29Fxxx are NOR Flash. 29L or LV parts are 3.3V and you want to stay away from those.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tmeeco.eu">http://www.tmeeco.eu</a><!-- m --></div>
